cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper is about end-to-end speech recognition using neural network models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and speech processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of different neural network architectures and their impact on performance, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper compares different models and their performance, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
